Representation.Label: monomorphic
Representation.Detail: Having one shape

Representation.Label: dimorphic
Representation.Detail: Having two shapes or sizes

Representation.Label: Architecture of fertile fronds
Representation.Detail: Architecture of the frond describes the global shape of the frond and the types of ramifications.

Representation.Label: digitate
Representation.Detail: Having four or more divisions all radiating narrowly from a single point, somewhate like the fingers of a hand

Representation.Label: palmate
Representation.Detail: Having four or more divisions radiating widely from a single point

Representation.Label: pinnate
Representation.Detail: Having two or more divisions on each side of a central axis that are not born from a single point

Representation.Label: paripinnate
Representation.Detail: Pinnate and terminated by a pair of pinnae similar to the lateral ones

Representation.Label: imparipinnate
Representation.Detail: Pinnate and terminated by a single pinna similar to the lateral ones

Representation.Label: ternate
Representation.Detail: Having three equal or subequal parts born from a single point at about right angles or nearly so to each other

Representation.Label: helicoid
Representation.Detail: Branching repeatedly only on the basiscopic side of the principal axis, and so appearing to have a dichotomously branched rachis

Representation.Label: geminate
Representation.Detail: borne in pairs

Representation.Label: Architecture of sterile fronds
Representation.Detail: Architecture of the frond describes the global shape of the frond and the types of ramifications.

Representation.Label: geminate
Representation.Detail: Borne in pairs

Representation.Label: Degree of division of lamina
Representation.Detail: The lamina of a frond is often divided into many pinnae along the length of the rachis. The pinnae can also be divided into many pinnules. Lamina may be simple (without division). If lamina is divided only into pinnae but the pinnae are not divided into pinnules then a frond is known as being pinnately divided. If a frond does have the second division into pinnules, it is bipinnately divided.

Representation.Label: 1-pinnate
Representation.Detail: Divided into entire to lobed pinnae that are contracted at the base

Representation.Label: 2-pinnate
Representation.Detail: Divided into pinnae bearing pinnules

Representation.Label: ≥ 3-pinnate
Representation.Detail: Several times divided (3 times or more)

Representation.Label: Degree of incision of the pinnae
Degree of incision of the pinnules
2-pinnate-entire
Representation.Detail: null

Representation.Label: Degree of incision of the pinnulules
Arrangement of lateral structures along the axis
alternate
Representation.Detail: Having one structure, in ferns usually a pinna, inserted at a single point along an axis

Representation.Label: opposite
Representation.Detail: Having two structures inserted opposite each other at a single pont along an axis

Representation.Label: Complete shape (frond)
Representation.Detail: The global form of the pinnae (or the last degree of frond division).

Representation.Label: Complete shape (pinnae/pinnules)
Representation.Detail: The global form of the pinnae (or the last degree of frond division).

Representation.Label: oblong
Representation.Detail: Longer than wide with the long sides parallel or nearly so and the end abrupt, rather than gradually tapered

Representation.Label: elliptic
Representation.Detail: Having the outline of a elongate circle

Representation.Label: lanceolate
Representation.Detail: Lance-shaped, with a long, tapering apex and a short-tapering base, thereforeest well above the base

Representation.Label: triangular
Representation.Detail: 3-angled, and so 3-sided

Representation.Label: linear
Representation.Detail: Long, narrow, and of uniform or nearly uniform width

Representation.Label: obovate
Representation.Detail: Spatula-shaped; narrow at the base and gradually wider distally to a rounded apex

Representation.Label: deltate
Representation.Detail: Broadly triangular with an obtuse apex

Representation.Label: falcate
Representation.Detail: Sickle- or scythe shaped; asymmetrically curved and tapered

Representation.Label: trapeziform
Representation.Detail: Having the outline of a trapezium, with four unequal sides, none of them parallel

Representation.Label: dimidiate
Representation.Detail: Halved diagonally, with usually one half rudimentary or partially absent

Representation.Label: lunulate
Representation.Detail: Shaped like a crescent or quarter-moon

Representation.Label: ovate
Representation.Detail: Having the outline of a longitudinal section of a hen's egg; similar to elliptical except broadest toward the base, rather than at the middle

Representation.Label: Base Form (pinnae/pinnules)
Representation.Detail: The shape of the basal side of the laminae (or the last division of the frond). Some shapes display one or two auriculates.

Representation.Label: simple
Representation.Detail: Without auricle

Representation.Label: auriculate
Representation.Detail: Bearing a rounded or sometimes elongate lobe or ear, usually at the base of a lamina, pinna or pinnule

Representation.Label: biauriculate
Representation.Detail: Bearing two auricles

Representation.Label: attenuate (θ<15°)
Representation.Detail: Forming an angle of less than 15°, norrowly tapering

Representation.Label: acuminate (15°<θ<30°)
Representation.Detail: Forming an angle of less than 30° with the sides somewhat concave

Representation.Label: cuneate (30°<θ<45°)
Representation.Detail: Forming an angle of 30-45° with the 2 sides straight; wedge-shaped

Representation.Label: acute (45°<θ<90°)
Representation.Detail: Forming an angle of 30-90° with the 2 sides straight or slightly convex

Representation.Label: obtuse (90°<θ<180°)
Representation.Detail: Forming an angle of 90° or more with the 2 sides straight of slightly convex

Representation.Label: truncate (θ=180°)
Representation.Detail: Appearing as if cut off perpendicular to the axis

Representation.Label: excavate
Representation.Detail: Having the basiscopic base cut away, usualy in a smooth curve

Representation.Label: cordate
Representation.Detail: Bearing a pair of broadly rounded, sometimes overlapping lobes

Representation.Label: hastate
Representation.Detail: Having the shape of an arrowhead, with laterally directed basal lobes

Representation.Label: attenuate (θ<15°; marging slightly convex)
Representation.Detail: Forming an angle of less than 15°, norrowly tapering

Representation.Label: accuminate (15°<θ<30°; marging slightly concave)
Representation.Detail: Forming an angle of less than 30° with the sides somewhat concave

Representation.Label: acute (30°<θ<90°)
Representation.Detail: Forming an angle of 30-90° with the 2 sides straight or slightly convex

Representation.Label: obtuse (90°<θ<180°)
Representation.Detail: Forming an angle of 90° or more with the 3 sides straight of slightly convex

Representation.Label: caudate
Representation.Detail: Bearing a narrow, elongate, tail-like appendage or apex

Representation.Label: apiculate
Representation.Detail: Abruptly terminating in a small, triangular apex

Representation.Label: mucronate
Representation.Detail: Bearing a short, stiff, bristle-like apical prolongation of a midrib costa or costule

Representation.Label: emarginate
Representation.Detail: Having a broad, shallow sinus at the nearly truncate apex of a segment, lobe, or tooth

Representation.Label: truncate
Representation.Detail: appearing as if cut off perpendicular to the axis

Representation.Label: translucent/thin
Representation.Detail: Sufficiently clear to pass light, but not a image

Representation.Label: opaque/thick
Representation.Detail: Not capable of transmitting light

Representation.Label: entire
Representation.Detail: null

Representation.Label: crenate
Representation.Detail: Rounded teeth, shallowly scalloped in a single plane

Representation.Label: serrulate
Representation.Detail: Having usually broad teeth on the margin directed acroscopically

Representation.Label: erose
Representation.Detail: Irregularly cut away and appearing eroded

Representation.Label: incised
Representation.Detail: Deeply, regularly and sharply cut

Representation.Label: laciniate
Representation.Detail: Cut into narrow lobes

Representation.Label: lacerate
Representation.Detail: Deeply and irregularly cut, almost torn

Representation.Label: glabrous
Representation.Detail: Lacking cilia

Representation.Label: ciliate
Representation.Detail: Flexible, thin, usually straight hairs

Representation.Label: setose
Representation.Detail: Stiff, thin, straight hairs

Representation.Label: cincinnate

Representation.Label: involucre (Hymenophyllaceae)
Representation.Detail: The tubular or bilabiate indisium in which the abaxial and adaxial portions are identical or nearly so (found in the hymenophyllaceae and some Dicksoniaceae and Dennstaedtiaceae)

Representation.Label: free bilabiate
Representation.Detail: Two-lipped involucres

Representation.Label: welded bilabiate
Representation.Detail: Having a form of an urn, constricted near the apex and tapered near the base

Representation.Label: epitactic
Representation.Detail: Bearing involucres on the apical veins of the catadromous fronds, pinnae, or pinnules (in Hymenophyllaceae)

Representation.Label: paratactic
Representation.Detail: Bearing involucres on the lateral veins of the anadromous pinnae or pinnules (in Hymenophyllaceae)

Representation.Label: pantotactic
Representation.Detail: Bearing involucres on the lateral and apical veins of the pinnae or pinnules (in Hymenophyllaceae)

Representation.Label: peltate
Representation.Detail: Round or nearly so and attached by a central pedicel
